254
00:31:20,084 --> 00:31:24,747
And my name is Melissa DeLay, and I'm the Senior Director of Service Planning for the MBTA.

255
00:31:25,307 --> 00:31:30,010
You're in the breakout room for Burlington, Medford, Winchester, and Woburn.

256
00:31:35,353 --> 00:31:45,077
So as Doug and Justin mentioned in the first part of the presentation, we did make meaningful changes to the network map based on the feedback that we received.

257
00:31:45,657 --> 00:31:50,139
Here's a sneak preview of some of the routes that we'll be talking about today here in this group.

258
00:31:50,979 --> 00:31:51,679
We have the 87, 89, 100, T101, 131, 134, 354,

259
00:32:00,384 --> 00:32:17,732
uh, 95, T96, 99, uh, and some others, uh, 80, 89, 134, uh, whether those were restorations of existing routes or route changes to better serve, uh, important, uh, destinations.

260
00:32:18,213 --> 00:32:22,875
Uh, in some case, those might be new routes added, but we did also have a few routes removed.

261
00:32:22,995 --> 00:32:25,797
So I do want to make sure we have ample time for questions.

262
00:32:25,977 --> 00:32:28,418
So I will jump in to the route-specific changes.

263
00:32:34,661 --> 00:32:42,905
So one of the biggest comments that we heard from Medford riders related to the T96.

264
00:32:43,865 --> 00:32:50,188
We heard that many riders of the 96 along Winthrop Street and George that had that the former proposal.

265
00:32:51,648 --> 00:32:54,289
would have kept service on College Ave.

266
00:32:54,950 --> 00:32:59,531
This was creating a hardship for them, and the walk was just too far, especially for seniors.

267
00:32:59,632 --> 00:33:08,855
So in this revised proposal, the T96 would serve High Street from Medford Square to Winthrop Circle, Winthrop Street, and George Street.

268
00:33:09,255 --> 00:33:18,739
This provides high frequency service to more riders, including some existing Route 94 riders near Winthrop Circle, and also current 96 riders along Winthrop Street

269
00:33:19,982 --> 00:33:22,924
right there, and George Street.

270
00:33:24,504 --> 00:33:39,411
Also, in the Somerville portion of the route, we also now propose a direct high-frequency connection between Davis Square, right there, and Union Square by extending the T96 terminus from Porter to East Somerville.

271
00:33:40,831 --> 00:33:44,353
That trip would have previously required a transfer in the original network.

272
00:33:49,917 --> 00:33:56,930
Next, the other biggest change I would say for the north side routes relates to the express route 354.

273
00:33:59,542 --> 00:34:03,063
In the original version of the network, there was no Express 354.

274
00:34:05,023 --> 00:34:11,544
We had redrawn the service to feed local service into the subways to the north.

275
00:34:12,084 --> 00:34:20,106
But one of the things that we heard a lot of was that the travel times were not competitive and there was a lot of interest in retaining the direct connection into downtown Boston.

276
00:34:20,746 --> 00:34:27,247
So in this revised proposal, the 354 would continue to do what it does today and would serve Burlington, Woburn,

277
00:34:28,293 --> 00:34:32,956
And Medford, Burlington and Woburn are shown on the right version of the map.

278
00:34:33,597 --> 00:34:39,641
And the Medford Square stop is shown on the left side of the map during rush hours on weekdays.

279
00:34:41,663 --> 00:34:49,088
There are a number of other network changes that flow from this, both from resources and also from a sort of service design.

280
00:34:49,168 --> 00:34:51,830
So I will get into those as we continue.

281
00:34:55,952 --> 00:35:03,099
Another of the major gaps that we had heard that we'd had in our initial version of the network was related to the route 80.

282
00:35:07,422 --> 00:35:16,906
We did not have the route 80 at all in our initial proposal due to substantial overlaps with the new Green Line extension that's slated to open later this year.

283
00:35:17,806 --> 00:35:29,190
But one of the gaps that this meant was that there is not a direct connection from Arlington Centre and Medford Street over to the new Medford Tufts Green Line station

284
00:35:29,670 --> 00:35:37,074
for 80 riders who might currently work near Lechmere or similar areas to be able to continue making their trips.

285
00:35:38,755 --> 00:35:53,923
In the revised proposal, we do restore the Route 80 connection from Arlington Center to Boston Ave and to Medford Tufts GLX station, and then we continue the service to Davis Square from Powder House for a redline connection.

286
00:35:54,617 --> 00:36:05,839
This also becomes the primary Boston Ave connection to the Greenline Extension Station at Medford Tufts, as this replaces the proposed 94 that had been on Boston Ave and which I have a slide on later.

287
00:36:08,420 --> 00:36:21,823
At the outer end of the Route 80, you also see that this is proposed to extend beyond Arlington to Winchester, Woburn, and Burlington as a 350 replacement

288
00:36:24,627 --> 00:36:28,092
to Burlington Mall Road, 3rd Ave, and North Burlington.

289
00:36:28,653 --> 00:36:38,088
And this would also provide those locations with both green line and red line connections at Medford Tufts and Davis in lieu of today's 350 connection at Ailey.

290
00:36:47,186 --> 00:36:50,608
Next, route 87 Arlington to Lechmere.

291
00:36:51,249 --> 00:36:54,771
We formally had proposed significant changes to route 87.

292
00:36:55,391 --> 00:36:57,192
You can see the original proposal on the left.

293
00:36:57,673 --> 00:37:05,818
However, we heard a lot from Somerville and Cambridge about this, especially on the loss of service to Market Basket from Clarendon Hill and Lechmere.

294
00:37:06,738 --> 00:37:15,180
On the Medford end, we also heard concerns about traffic and congestion on Harvard Street and with the loss of service on Mystic Ave north of Harvard Street.

295
00:37:15,640 --> 00:37:31,383
So in this proposal, we've restored the Route 87 as a direct route from Arlington Center to Lechmere Station seven days a week, which is actually different than today's 87 that only operates to Arlington Center six days a week and terminates at Clarendon Hill on Sundays.

296
00:37:33,238 --> 00:37:42,061
This does mean that there would be no service on Harvard Street in Medford where we had proposed running new service and we would maintain service on Mystic Ave in Medford.

297
00:37:42,081 --> 00:37:43,821
That's the section here.

298
00:37:45,542 --> 00:37:48,403
Mystic Ave in Medford and Somerville via the 95.

299
00:37:52,107 --> 00:37:53,428
So here's the route 95.

300
00:37:53,888 --> 00:38:13,078
Because we restored the 87 to Lechmere, which took buses off of Mystic Ave, we are restoring the 95 to continue providing service on Mystic Ave towards Sullivan, as shown on the right, which serves parts of Medford poised for a substantial redevelopment, and is similar to what most 95 trips do today.

301
00:38:13,698 --> 00:38:17,480
Compared to today's 95, there would be one consistent service pattern.

302
00:38:17,861 --> 00:38:19,221
The route would go from Arlington,

303
00:38:21,065 --> 00:38:28,747
Arlington to Sullivan consistently, rather than the current service pattern where some trips start in Arlington and some start on Placestead Road.

304
00:38:32,528 --> 00:38:41,050
Also, the frequency of this route is slated to improve to every 20 minutes, mostly seven days a week, with some every 30 minutes service after 10pm.

305
00:38:41,571 --> 00:38:46,912
This fills in a gap between the three new high frequency corridors that are proposed in Medford.

306
00:38:53,262 --> 00:38:57,186
Next, we have bus route 89 and T101.

307
00:38:58,547 --> 00:39:08,677
One of the other biggest things that we heard in Somerville and Medford was the lack of connection in our original map between Winter Hill, Ball Square, and Davis Square.

308
00:39:09,337 --> 00:39:17,225
On the left, you can see our original proposal, which had new high-frequency routes, but no 89 toward Davis and no bus connections at Ball Square.

309
00:39:18,153 --> 00:39:28,924
In the new map on the right, you can see the proposed Route 89, which would operate consistently with a single service pattern between Davis and Sullivan, with a stop near Ball Square Station on the Green Line.

310
00:39:29,705 --> 00:39:36,011
For Route 89 users, note that there would not be a mix of some Clarendon Hill trips and some Davis trips.

311
00:39:36,692 --> 00:39:41,637
For connections to Clarendon Hill, please use the 87 or 90 and connect at Davis.

312
00:39:42,740 --> 00:39:52,448
Now, as a result of the 89 restoration, we have also proposed keeping the T-101 route on Main Street, that's this stretch right here.

313
00:39:53,289 --> 00:40:08,282
You can see it had been sort of squared off to serve Lagoon Square here, but we're proposing to keep it doing what it does today, using the stretch of Main Street, which serves a little farther north on the Medford side of Winter Hill, while the 89 will serve Lagoon Square on Broadway.

314
00:40:14,650 --> 00:40:15,033
Roots 94 and 134.

315
00:40:18,762 --> 00:40:19,943
This one gets a little complicated.

316
00:40:20,083 --> 00:40:28,426
So the 94 formerly had been proposed as shown on the left to connect Burlington Mall to Davis via Woburn and Winchester.

317
00:40:28,926 --> 00:40:37,970
And the mall had been separated from the other 350 Burlington local service to make both services more direct and appealing as an express service replacement.

318
00:40:38,670 --> 00:40:45,673
Now that there is no route 94 in the revised proposal, instead, we propose restoring the route 134 from North Woburn

319
00:40:48,448 --> 00:40:54,571
to Winchester, Medford, and Wellington Station, along with changes to the 80 and 354.

320
00:40:54,671 --> 00:40:57,033
There's a few reasons for this.

321
00:40:57,713 --> 00:41:05,497
One, there was a problem with the original Route 94 and the turns near West Medford Station due to the railroad crossing and intersection geometry.

322
00:41:06,498 --> 00:41:14,322
Also, we had a lot of interest in restoring the Route 354 express route in Burlington, but that led to other network changes as a resource offset.

323
00:41:15,855 --> 00:41:20,539
Then there was the extension of the Route 80 to Burlington Mall that I spoke about on an earlier slide.

324
00:41:21,339 --> 00:41:36,271
And I do want to note that with this change, nearly all of the proposed 94 is covered now by the new proposed 80, 134, and 354, except for Placestead Road and Medford, which would not have direct service.

325
00:41:36,771 --> 00:41:41,955
It's entirely within 0.5 miles of other bus service on High Street or Winter Street.

326
00:41:43,450 --> 00:41:52,332
Also note that the proposed 134 on the right would be a little different than today's 134, and that it's proposed to go down Locust Street in Medford near the Wegmans.

327
00:41:53,052 --> 00:42:01,775
It also would have more consistent service with more full trips and fewer of those short trips on nights and weekends that only go as far as Medford Square.

328
00:42:07,036 --> 00:42:09,657
Next, we have some changes in Medford to the 99 and 108.

329
00:42:11,842 --> 00:42:18,546
Bus route 99 was proposed as shown on the left and would serve Middlesex Ave in Medford and Wellington station.

330
00:42:19,066 --> 00:42:41,177
Based on feedback that we heard regarding the loss of service to Commercial Street near the Super 88, Medford Street near some medical facilities, Cambridge Health Alliance and others, and also other locations in Everett from current 97 riders, we've extended the 99 as shown in the center map like a 97 through Everett to the Gateway Center and on to Wellington.

331
00:42:42,992 --> 00:42:51,661
The Middlesex Ave portion of the route would still be served by the extended 108, as shown on the right, which had formerly terminated at Malden.

332
00:42:51,781 --> 00:43:02,051
So overall, we end up with kind of one more segment of route in the mix, which allows us to get closer service right over here to the

333
00:43:05,324 --> 00:43:14,453
to the Super 88 and over here for some of those other medical facilities and other locations, getting folks within.

334
00:43:20,159 --> 00:43:28,788
Bus route 100, this had been proposed to continue via the current terminus near Elm Street and then across to Governor's Ave.

335
00:43:30,027 --> 00:43:37,388
over by Lawrence Memorial Hospital, and then up Winthrop Street near Medford High School, terminating near Playstead Road.

336
00:43:39,049 --> 00:43:45,910
Since it's part of the other changes, we have restored the 134 to connect Wellington to Medford Square and Winthrop Street.

337
00:43:47,130 --> 00:43:49,391
This stretch here is now covered by the 134.

338
00:43:50,131 --> 00:43:54,652
We've proposed that the 100 should terminate as it does today near Elm Street.

339
00:43:54,832 --> 00:43:57,012
There would be no service on Governor's Ave.

340
00:44:03,472 --> 00:44:05,593
bus routes 133 and 131.

341
00:44:07,854 --> 00:44:10,234
The 133 initial proposed route is shown on the left.

342
00:44:11,135 --> 00:44:19,097
In the new network, there is no route 133, but we have modified our proposed 131 route to provide some of the functionality.

343
00:44:20,598 --> 00:44:32,062
So the 133 did include a new service to Anderson-Woburn commuter rail and had been part of a package of changes to create more local bus service instead of the express services in Burlington and Woburn.

344
00:44:32,818 --> 00:44:41,661
However, with the restoration of the 354 express route, one of the trade-offs that we made was to truncate new service extensions.

345
00:44:42,081 --> 00:44:45,683
So you can see that we're no longer showing bus service to Anderson-Woburn.

346
00:44:48,844 --> 00:44:55,086
North Woburn service will be part of the restored 134 route that I spoke about previously here.

347
00:44:56,295 --> 00:45:08,474
The local Woburn, Stoneham, and Melrose connection will be part of the Route 131 that also serves more of the east side Melrose rather than being a dedicated new Route 133.

348
00:45:15,602 --> 00:45:18,724
So I promised I'd keep these as brief as I could.

349
00:45:19,685 --> 00:45:23,568
So now we want to make sure we have time for your questions.

350
00:45:24,909 --> 00:45:36,238
So if you can, please, if you're at a computer, you can enter your comments, questions into the chat and be sure to select

351
00:45:37,519 --> 00:45:39,400
Don't direct message me personally.

352
00:45:39,460 --> 00:45:41,902
We have a team of folks who's helping to facilitate this.

353
00:45:42,022 --> 00:45:48,548
So send your message to the person who is named ask questions here co-host.

354
00:45:49,709 --> 00:45:56,014
And they will help to facilitate getting your questions answered or your comments recorded.

355
00:45:58,200 --> 00:46:06,689
We've already gotten some questions in, so everyone can continue to put your questions in the chat to ask questions here, but the first one, I'll start with an easy one.

356
00:46:07,270 --> 00:46:09,592
What does the T in the bus route name stand for?

357
00:46:09,632 --> 00:46:10,173
For example, T96.

358
00:46:12,279 --> 00:46:13,240
That's a great question.

359
00:46:13,320 --> 00:46:15,602
So that's a working name.

360
00:46:16,022 --> 00:46:28,232
I don't know that that's going to be the final name once we get to everything, but we wanted to symbolize for any of those high frequency routes that these were something different, that these are the routes where you don't even need to look at a schedule card.

361
00:46:28,272 --> 00:46:36,139
You can just sort of show up the way that you might show up for the number one bus or the 77 or a number of our other high frequency services.

362
00:46:37,019 --> 00:46:38,460
We'd also debated calling it

363
00:46:39,241 --> 00:46:44,464
high frequency, let's call it the F route, but that could have kind of a negative connotation.

364
00:46:44,544 --> 00:46:58,191
So we were sort of thinking that we could riff off of, you know, how people talk about generally when they're taking the subway, they want to take the T, but we wanted to emphasize that all of our modes, even bus modes, can have high quality, high frequency service.

365
00:46:58,271 --> 00:47:07,795
So it was riffing off of our name, the T, but it really just symbolizes that it's a high frequency route and the name might change.

366
00:47:07,855 --> 00:47:08,856
That's a placeholder.

367
00:47:11,024 --> 00:47:11,544
Okay, thanks.

368
00:47:11,705 --> 00:47:16,428
We also have a few questions around West Medford, specifically around the 94 bus.

369
00:47:16,528 --> 00:47:19,470
So I'll start with the first one.

370
00:47:19,490 --> 00:47:27,777
How will individuals in West Medford readily access Davis Square and the Red Line, particularly MGH, without the 94 bus line?

371
00:47:28,477 --> 00:47:33,261
And how will they access the Green Line at Tufts University Medford Station?

372
00:47:34,882 --> 00:47:35,262
That's fair.

373
00:47:37,045 --> 00:47:39,506
Let me pull up one of the previous slides.

374
00:47:39,566 --> 00:47:50,911
But if there's a different route, I can also pull up our Remix map that we've been using to show things.

375
00:47:52,712 --> 00:47:58,995
Let me actually switch to my 80 and my 96 map.

376
00:48:01,278 --> 00:48:05,919
So for part, it depends on which part of the 94 you're coming from.

377
00:48:07,560 --> 00:48:18,322
If you're on the section between High Street, between Medford Square and Winthrop, that would be a case of being able to switch to using the new 96.

378
