570
01:11:46,247 --> 01:12:00,718
The only direct connection to downtown Boston that we're showing is the Express 354, which is pretty much a continuation of what we do today with having the 354 make the stop in Medford Square, but that just serves Medford Square directly.

571
01:12:01,539 --> 01:12:02,320
That doesn't serve

572
01:12:03,140 --> 01:12:08,443
farther out on Salem Street or Playstead Road or High Street and some of the other locations.

573
01:12:08,883 --> 01:12:18,588
Instead, we've really reoriented the network around Medford to have more high-frequency connections, more all-day connections.

574
01:12:19,009 --> 01:12:25,152
And overall, there's more service that we're showing on the map in Medford than there was pre-COVID.

575
01:12:25,992 --> 01:12:28,614
We wanted to be a network that works seven days a week.

576
01:12:29,754 --> 01:12:45,924
and takes advantage of the new Green Line connection so that it can really be a feeder into these resources, the Red Line and the Green Line and the Orange Line that are so close by, rather than having the express services, which are more costly to operate.

577
01:12:47,825 --> 01:12:55,129
But we recognize that those are also very popular, which is why we did restore the Medford Square express stop.

578
01:12:59,201 --> 01:13:01,903
And what's the frequency and span of the 354?

579
01:13:02,784 --> 01:13:05,466
It's similar to what it is today.

580
01:13:05,787 --> 01:13:09,590
So it's about every 30 minutes, but it's rush hours only.

581
01:13:11,071 --> 01:13:18,057
So this at a very broad strokes level is showing six to 9 a.m.

582
01:13:18,377 --> 01:13:22,781
and four to seven, but it would be largely similar to what's operating today.

583
01:13:23,562 --> 01:13:27,125
Some of these buckets don't take those too literally.

584
01:13:28,307 --> 01:13:32,774
These were sort of simplifications that we used for the overall resource estimation.

