1154
02:17:24,673 --> 02:17:39,937
why you would want a system where people are now increasing traffic, increasing carbon emissions by driving, or just not going into downtown at all, when I thought what we were trying to do was make downtown Boston a viable financial center and a viable place where people wanted to go.

1155
02:17:41,158 --> 02:17:44,619
So there are several problems with what the plan is.

1156
02:17:44,679 --> 02:17:52,481
And let me just say this, that I don't see a single improvement to any MBTA service, bus service in Newton, none.

1157
02:17:52,986 --> 02:17:55,267
They are all deterioration, they are all negatives.

1158
02:17:55,888 --> 02:17:57,909
And I think that is really a shame.

1159
02:17:58,029 --> 02:18:09,495
So the problems are the 553, 554, 556, 558, they're all local buses, as you know, and don't go downtown.

1160
02:18:09,835 --> 02:18:14,257
So what that means effectively is that adds at least half an hour to the commute.

1161
02:18:14,658 --> 02:18:17,879
And I know that because I have tried to take the 553 and 554 over the past few months.

1162
02:18:19,337 --> 02:18:22,660
I have gone during rush hour, the height of rush hour, quarter to eight in the morning.

1163
02:18:22,740 --> 02:18:30,226
I have waited, I would say, between 25 minutes and 40 minutes each time in Newton Corner for the bus to go downtown.

1164
02:18:30,266 --> 02:18:38,573
There was not a single bus going downtown at quarter to eight in the morning to a quarter after eight in the morning.

1165
02:18:38,674 --> 02:18:41,156
For that period, not a single bus going downtown.

1166
02:18:41,896 --> 02:18:46,220
So the idea that there's gonna be more frequent buses is just not happening.

1167
02:18:46,847 --> 02:18:55,953
And the buses that the 553, 554 used to run every 10 or 15 minutes during rush hour, it now runs, I think, once an hour.

1168
02:18:56,533 --> 02:19:03,938
And then if you make that, you have to wait, as I said, for 25 to 40 minutes for a bus to get downtown that stops in Copley.

1169
02:19:04,298 --> 02:19:11,463
So you're adding half an hour, it took me an hour and a half to get to work one day using the express bus that used to take me 35 minutes.

1170
02:19:13,486 --> 02:19:14,187
after 40 minutes.

1171
02:19:14,387 --> 02:19:19,450
So it's not surprising that you're not seeing the ridership bounce back because people are not willing to do that.

1172
02:19:19,710 --> 02:19:20,971
And if they can work from home, they will.

1173
02:19:21,212 --> 02:19:22,372
If they can drive, they will.

1174
02:19:22,793 --> 02:19:23,873
And so that's what's happening.

1175
02:19:24,054 --> 02:19:27,196
And I see that as a large problem.

1176
02:19:27,216 --> 02:19:34,661
And I don't understand why we are not trying to encourage people taking public transportation and people going back downtown.

1177
02:19:34,701 --> 02:19:37,083
I understand there's always resource concerns.

1178
02:19:37,479 --> 02:19:47,421
And I totally support the idea of having an equitable bus system and making sure that people who have no other options and need the bus to get wherever they need to go should certainly have that service.

1179
02:19:47,881 --> 02:19:50,041
But I don't see why it has to be an either or.

1180
02:19:50,061 --> 02:19:55,822
The state just passed a millionaires tax where the money is supposed to go for public transportation.

1181
02:19:56,062 --> 02:20:00,283
We have a climate crisis where we want to decrease the amount of carbon emissions.

1182
02:20:00,643 --> 02:20:03,543
This just makes no sense to me whatsoever.

1183
02:20:03,563 --> 02:20:06,044
And I also want to say, and I think that,

1184
02:20:07,939 --> 02:20:17,767
Our elected representatives have also said this, that there are hundreds of units of housing that are going up along Washington Street in Newton, many of them affordable housing.

1185
02:20:18,087 --> 02:20:24,812
The armory, I was on the citizens committee for that, and the city decided to buy that building.

1186
02:20:24,852 --> 02:20:29,856
There's gonna be, I don't remember exactly how many, but something like 50, 60 units of affordable housing next door.

1187
02:20:29,876 --> 02:20:33,839
There are gonna be 400 units of housing that are gonna be built very soon.

1188
02:20:33,860 --> 02:20:36,942
And the north side of Newton,

1189
02:20:37,476 --> 02:20:40,278
is not the wealthy side of Newton, put it that way.

1190
02:20:40,898 --> 02:20:45,942
There's many low-income families that live within walking distance of that area.

1191
02:20:46,462 --> 02:20:48,263
And they won't be able to walk.

1192
02:20:48,483 --> 02:20:51,465
So I just want to ask you to reconsider.

1193
02:20:51,525 --> 02:20:58,430
And I do want to ask you, I'd like an answer as to why are you destroying the Newton Express bus system?

1194
02:20:58,470 --> 02:21:00,031
I still haven't really heard an answer to that.

1195
02:21:00,071 --> 02:21:01,192
So I would like an answer to that.

1196
02:21:01,272 --> 02:21:01,552
Thank you.

1197
02:21:05,853 --> 02:21:07,054
Thank you for your comments.

1198
02:21:08,055 --> 02:21:10,778
Oh, I have a little bit of an echo.

1199
02:21:13,822 --> 02:21:18,187
So I'm going to turn it to Terry Alther.

1200
02:21:18,307 --> 02:21:19,589
Terry, I'm going to unmute you.

1201
02:21:22,393 --> 02:21:23,253
Thank you very much.

1202
02:21:24,074 --> 02:21:36,138
I just want to say that I strongly echo the comments of my fellow Newton resident who just spoke as with the other elected officials from Newton to support more express bus services.

1203
02:21:36,258 --> 02:21:38,299
While I fortunately do live near the 505,

1204
02:21:39,819 --> 02:21:53,022
I will say during midday when there's no 505 service and when the commuter rail only goes one day, I will say back when the 553, 554 went downtown, that was extremely beneficial during midday when I had to do a downtown trip.

1205
02:21:55,303 --> 02:22:00,504
Going off that, I do think that there's definitely concerns I have about the plan overall.

1206
02:22:00,644 --> 02:22:03,585
I do think there's a very strong austerity mindset to it.

1207
02:22:03,685 --> 02:22:07,305
As a result, there's very much a lot of communities are pitted against each other.

1208
02:22:07,866 --> 02:22:08,826
Obviously, I think that

1209
02:22:09,946 --> 02:22:31,647
Recent revision I think for the most part, I think was much more beneficial for certain communities including Newton, although I will say that some changes such as having the 52 be a weekday only route, and then having a 59 still do that deviation through Adam Street instead of just keeping the current alignment do baffle me a little bit and

1210
02:22:31,987 --> 02:22:40,429
And I know especially my friends in Newton Center are disappointed to learn that the 60 will not be extended to Newton Center after all.

1211
02:22:41,129 --> 02:22:48,551
I will say I do think that there's a lot of considerations that haven't been considered in this proposal.

1212
02:22:49,371 --> 02:22:55,953
First of which is obviously the new projects to repair and improve I-90.

1213
02:22:56,093 --> 02:23:00,914
So especially while that's going on, I think it's vital to ensure we have as many express buses as possible.

1214
02:23:02,074 --> 02:23:12,883
that there's been people advocating to have HOV lanes precisely for that purpose on I-90, for the buses to easily get through and through traffic as well.

1215
02:23:13,263 --> 02:23:20,889
I've ridden the 505 recently during rush hour traffic heading into Boston in the evening, and the fact that it was super crowded pretty much

1216
02:23:22,630 --> 02:23:27,592
makes the case on its own, especially since most of the rush hour traffic is heading westbound.

1217
02:23:28,452 --> 02:23:40,736
But yeah, I also strongly believe that with this new plan, I think it's vital to work with other transit agencies.

1218
02:23:41,056 --> 02:23:48,238
While I'm pleased to know that the 53 will be an option to ride heading into

1219
02:23:49,298 --> 02:24:08,569
Yeah, tending into that area of like Western wall fam, especially in market basket, which I, which I sometimes go to, I will say that I wish there's a way to ensure that with the 53 that we can do connections with the 1 and the 8 of Metro West regional transit agency, because sometimes I do have to head out.

1220
02:24:09,550 --> 02:24:23,465
to westwards and especially in the morning on weekdays, that's extremely difficult because of the fact that the commuter rail trains in West Newton are only going into Boston and there's very few outbound trains that even stop at Boston if at all.

1221
02:24:24,646 --> 02:24:27,710
I will also note that I do think that

1222
02:24:28,748 --> 02:24:43,433
If there's a way to better coordinate this with officials, I think it's useful because I know there's certain comments that were made throughout this presentation that there are people who are unhappy with the changes, they should talk to their elected officials, which I think I definitely will do.

1223
02:24:45,365 --> 02:25:05,130
I think that it'd be really useful because I think especially with the change on Adams Street for the 59, I think that if it's really that much traffic, I think it'd be very useful to at least have a bus route that goes from Newton Corner through Adams Street to maybe at the very least near that area where BJ's is at.

1224
02:25:05,150 --> 02:25:11,371
Because I know there are a lot of people who shop in that area, whether it be Shaw's, BJ's, or Stop and Shop as well.

1225
02:25:13,792 --> 02:25:31,415
Should definitely be considered and yeah, I hope that if there's if the issue is a funding issue, or if it's a shortage issue that this gets the MBTA make specific requests to the state legislature, because I think with the current trends going on, I think those requests will be made.

1226
02:25:32,827 --> 02:25:37,188
All right, I think you, you kind of, I think you were finishing up, even though it cut out at the end.

1227
02:25:37,228 --> 02:25:38,369
So, thank you for your comment.

1228
02:25:38,989 --> 02:25:42,850
I will make a, I know there's a lot of people who still want to speak tonight.

1229
02:25:42,970 --> 02:25:46,351
So I would urge everyone if you could keep your comments.

1230
02:25:47,831 --> 02:25:49,872
Relatively brief, that would be helpful.

1231
02:25:49,892 --> 02:25:51,992
So we can hear from as many people as possible.

1232
02:25:52,873 --> 02:25:57,494
So, um, I have Daniel next and I'm going to unmute Daniel.

1233
02:26:00,735 --> 02:26:00,915
Hi.

1234
02:26:02,330 --> 02:26:02,790
