1235
02:26:03,891 --> 02:26:04,812
Yes, you're all set.

1236
02:26:04,872 --> 02:26:05,212
Perfect.

1237
02:26:05,932 --> 02:26:09,575
Um, thank you guys so much for everything you've been doing with the, with the buses and the changes and everything.

1238
02:26:10,379 --> 02:26:12,921
I had two, well, one comment and one question.

1239
02:26:13,022 --> 02:26:30,676
My first question was about after this is proposed to the board and then they give feedback and such, will there be any other rounds of feedback or opportunities for the public to give their input or is it just that is if approved, what is gonna be instated over the next several years?

1240
02:26:31,717 --> 02:26:33,719
So I was wondering if that could be answered.

1241
02:26:35,470 --> 02:26:43,234
Thank you, Daniel for your question this is a sort of similar question to the one we got from the Medford City Councilor earlier there.

1242
02:26:44,295 --> 02:26:50,419
When we go to implement go through the phases of implementation, we will be looking at.

1243
02:26:51,635 --> 02:27:07,271
the conditions that exist on the ground, how it's compared to what existed when we made this proposal, and if we need to make any modifications to the network as proposed based on those changes.

1244
02:27:09,678 --> 02:27:16,000
Part of that will be folks submitting comments to us with their thoughts on implementation.

1245
02:27:16,080 --> 02:27:26,062
We have an online feedback form open now that folks can submit comments to, to the implementation team.

1246
02:27:26,703 --> 02:27:37,666
So we are continuously receiving feedback from folks and we'll continue to receive feedback from folks as we go through that implementation process.

1247
02:27:38,486 --> 02:27:38,886
I can't

1248
02:27:39,799 --> 02:27:58,221
make promises about any particular changes to the network, but I can say realistically we know that over a five-year implementation timeline, some circumstances will change over that period that have implications for what we ultimately implement.

1249
02:27:59,744 --> 02:28:04,811
and what the network finally looks like at that year five mark.

1250
02:28:05,092 --> 02:28:11,843
So we will continue to accept comments from folks and there'll be continuous communications about this process as it moves forward.

1251
02:28:13,055 --> 02:28:13,716
Great, thank you.

1252
02:28:13,796 --> 02:28:29,890
And then the other thing I wanted to bring up was kind of echo what partially what was mentioned earlier about the 83 bus specifically, that I live between Inman and Porter and that's a great bus going to Central, but I was also really happy to see that the bus was potentially going to be going to Kendall also.

1253
02:28:30,371 --> 02:28:32,693
And I was wondering if there are ever any routes that like

1254
02:28:33,486 --> 02:28:45,077
or that you guys would ever consider implementing something such that like the bus went from Central to Rindge and then Rindge to Kendall, then Kendall back to Rindge and kind of did an alternating thing.

1255
02:28:45,117 --> 02:28:52,764
I know that could be confusing if we're the same number bus, but just an idea there, just because I have found it quite difficult to get to Kendall kind of from that.

1256
02:28:54,187 --> 02:29:02,094
area between Porter and Inman Square, especially with the new proposal of the 85 that would come only every hour or so.

1257
02:29:02,394 --> 02:29:07,919
So taking the 83 there just would result in about 15, 20 minutes of walking or waiting up to an hour for a bus.

1258
02:29:08,019 --> 02:29:10,101
So just wanted to throw that out there as something else.

1259
02:29:10,161 --> 02:29:12,323
But thank you guys for all of your input and stuff.

1260
02:29:12,843 --> 02:29:14,865
Thank you for your suggestions as well, Daniel.

1261
02:29:16,166 --> 02:29:20,910
I'm going to now turn to Katie P. I'm going to unmute you, Katie.

1262
02:29:22,537 --> 02:29:23,657
Hi, yes, thank you.

1263
02:29:24,698 --> 02:29:29,459
First, I wanted to say I appreciate the revisions that you made to the T-96 route.

1264
02:29:30,899 --> 02:29:44,782
I currently live in Medford Hillside neighborhood, and I find that even with that revision to serve the Winthrop Street part of that route, our neighborhood has had a lot of service taken away from it.

1265
02:29:45,142 --> 02:29:52,064
And there's a pretty gaping hole in the map in terms of Medford Hillside, Western Somerville, West Medford.

1266
02:29:53,545 --> 02:30:12,377
And I think a big concern about this is that a lot of my neighbors do not have cars and because we've had previous multiple reliable bus service to get us specifically to Davis Square, and to Arlington Center, and to West Medford, and especially along Boston Avenue.

1267
02:30:13,438 --> 02:30:28,638
I think there's a concern because when we were in the breakout rooms, the answer to a question about this was, oh, you can take the at which I appreciate you having reinstated however the 80s route is now incredibly long going all the way out to Burlington mall

1268
02:30:29,359 --> 02:30:31,881
And that's the only route that's serving this entire neighborhood.

1269
02:30:31,901 --> 02:30:33,942
And so that is a little troublesome when you're,

1270
02:30:56,457 --> 02:31:03,043
I have a lot of neighbors who are senior citizens and live in the affordable housing, and walk, walking court.

1271
02:31:03,824 --> 02:31:11,991
And that is the, the only bus that would be serving that neighborhood currently with the new route and, you know, I feel like that's

1272
02:31:14,033 --> 02:31:17,455
Unfair access for them and for our entire neighborhood.

1273
02:31:17,976 --> 02:31:29,783
So I would really hope that you would at least consider increasing the frequency of the at, because that's a really, really important route, incredibly important all my neighbors take it all the time.

1274
02:31:30,543 --> 02:31:38,145
And I think the answer in the breakouts, I was saying, oh, we will just have to, once it's instated, then maybe it'll be increased based on ridership.

1275
02:31:38,185 --> 02:31:41,966
But when it's only that infrequent, riders don't take it.

1276
02:31:42,126 --> 02:31:55,549
That's, I think that's the issue is that if you have to wait 30 minutes for a bus that may or may not be late because it's coming all the way from Burlington, you might try to find some alternate route, which would be way more expensive, like taking an Uber or not.

1277
02:31:55,629 --> 02:31:59,950
And so I think that's an unreliable way to try to possibly change that route.

1278
02:32:00,650 --> 02:32:03,732
Perhaps you can consider just increasing that frequency.

1279
02:32:05,113 --> 02:32:05,413
Thank you.

1280
02:32:05,833 --> 02:32:06,494
Thank you, Katie.

1281
02:32:06,514 --> 02:32:08,015
I appreciate your comments tonight.

1282
02:32:09,716 --> 02:32:11,857
I'm going to go to Gregory Zelt.

1283
02:32:12,978 --> 02:32:14,419
Gregory, you should be able to speak now.

1284
02:32:17,961 --> 02:32:18,901
