1322
02:35:01,736 --> 02:35:04,437
Thank you for holding this meeting and for allowing public comment.

1323
02:35:05,297 --> 02:35:10,140
I wanted to speak about the reduction of service to West Cambridge in particular.

1324
02:35:11,601 --> 02:35:22,507
First of all, I don't feel like very many people knew about this whole situation because when I found out about it, it was already very late.

1325
02:35:22,607 --> 02:35:24,268
It was the end of summer, kind of September.

1326
02:35:24,628 --> 02:35:33,111
And then when I brought it up to people in the neighborhood, particularly parents, parents of the high school students, it seemed like nobody knew about it.

1327
02:35:33,271 --> 02:35:34,352
So that's one thing.

1328
02:35:35,252 --> 02:35:39,834
Maybe because, you know, the kids who take the buses don't, you know, don't pay attention to this kind of thing.

1329
02:35:39,854 --> 02:35:40,794
I don't really know.

1330
02:35:41,254 --> 02:35:43,496
but it seemed like people were not aware.

1331
02:35:44,476 --> 02:35:55,222
So the reduction in services, I wanted to talk about how it affects the CRLS students, the students in the high school, because they don't have school buses.

1332
02:35:55,282 --> 02:35:57,704
We do rely on public transportation.

1333
02:35:58,004 --> 02:35:59,687
transit for the kids to get to school.

1334
02:36:01,029 --> 02:36:13,106
And at this point already, just from, you know, all the parents have reached out to me, I know that the service is already unreliable enough to the point that kids

1335
02:36:13,667 --> 02:36:21,192
don't rely on the public bus to go to school anymore because they wait for the bus and then it doesn't show up and then they're late to school.

1336
02:36:21,212 --> 02:36:23,693
And so then the next day they're like, mom, drive me or whatever.

1337
02:36:23,713 --> 02:36:28,496
And so it becomes very, very hard to use it.

1338
02:36:29,897 --> 02:36:38,723
And as it becomes even less frequent with the reductions that are coming up in the 78 in particular, I worry that people are just gonna

1339
02:36:39,283 --> 02:36:41,904
you know, kind of drop it from their list of options.

1340
02:36:42,044 --> 02:37:03,955
I think a couple of other people brought this up already, is that when you have a bus that has service that's running less than, you know, twice an hour, say, or, you know, something, there aren't buses that are coming to your neighborhood in any kind of regular, you know, every 15 minutes kind of way, then you can't really rely on it to get to school on time, or to get, you know, home on time, to get to your, you know, activity on time.

1341
02:37:04,015 --> 02:37:07,617
